==Parts-of-speech==

* <n>      Noun
* <np>     Proper noun
* <vblex>  Verb 

* <num>    Numeral
* <det>    Determiner
* <prn>    Pronoun
* <post>   Postposition
* <part>   Particle
* <cnjcoo> Co-ordinating conjunction
* <cnjsub> Sub-ordinating conjunction

==Post-positions==

===Orthography===

Monosyllabic postpositions are joined to the stem, polysyllabic are written separately.

* ykuápe 
  ykuá+pe

* akaru hagua

===Examples===

* pe [a | en, in | to | at]
* gua [de, of | from (origin)]
* guý [debajo de, under]
* a [sobre, on]
* ari [sobre, on]
* re [en | para, in | for] 

* hagua [para, for]
* ndive [con, with]
* pegua [de, from (origin)]
* kupe [detras de, behind]
* tenonde [delante, in front of]
* ykere [al lado de, beside | next to]
* pype [dentro, inside]
* hyepype [adentro, inside]
* apytepe [en medio de, between]

==Nouns==

* mitã [niño, child]
* jagua [perro, dog]
* kure [cerdo, pig]
* mbarakaja [gato, cat]
* vaka [vaca, cow]
* kavaju [caballo, horse]
* tarave [cucaracha, cockroach]
* taguato [ , eagle]
* ka'i [mono, monkey]
* apere'a [conejo, rabbit]
* tetã [país, country]
* jyva [brazo, arm]
* óga [casa, house
* yvyra [árbol, tree]
* tape [camino, way]
* aravo [hora, hour]
* tata [fuego, fire]
* táva [ciudad, city]
* ysyry [río, river]


==Proper names==

* Tetã Paraguái [República del Paraguay]
* Tetã Volivia [Republica del Bolivia]

==Demonstratives==

===Concrete (presencia)===

* pe [eso, that]
* ko [este, this]
* umi [esos, those]
* â [estos, these]
* ko'â [estos, these] 
* amo [aquel, that one]

===Abstract (ausencia)===

* ku [ese, that]
* upe [ese, that]
* aipo [aquel, that one]
* ako [aquel, that one]

==Quantifiers==

* heta [many, much]

==Interrogatives==

* mboy [cuanto, how many]  "Mboypa ne memby?", "Cuantos hijos tiene Ud.?"
* mba'éicha [cómo, how]
* moó [dónde, where]
* mba'e [qué, what]

==Numerals==

* mokói [dos]

==Pronouns==

===Personal===
* p1.mf.sg 	Che
* p2.mf.sg 	Nde
* p3.mf.sg 	Ha'e
* incl.p1.mf.pl Ñande
* excl.p1.mf.pl Ore
* p2.mf.pl	Peê
* p3.mf.pl	Ha'eKuera

==Definite==

* mayma -- [todos, cada uno]

==Verbs==

* Cheréra [Me llamo]
  Che+réra

* nderéra [Te llamas]
  nde+réra 

===Prefixes===

* Che areko   [yo tengo]
  Che a+reko 

* Nde rereko  [tu tienes]
  Nde re+reko

* Ha'e oreko  [el/ella tiene]
  Ha'e o+reko

* Ñande jareko [nosotros (incl.) tenemos]
        ja+reko
 
        ñañe'é [nosotros (incl.) hablamos]
        ña+ñe'é

* Ore roreko   [nosotros (excl. tenemos]
      ro+reko

* Peé pereko   [vosotros tenéis]
      pe+reko

* Ha'ekuéra oreko [ellos tienen]
            o+reko
==Conjunctions==

===Coordinators===

* ha [y, and]


===Subordinators===


* -ramo [cuando | si, when | if]

==Sample texts==

===UDHR Article 1===

Mayma yvypóra ou ko     yvy ári iñapyty'yre ha eteîcha 

Todo  hombre     este       sobre            y  igualmente

tecoruvicharendá ha acatúape      jeguerekópe; ha ikatu 
                                          
libertad?         y derecha+EN            +EN; y  (es) posible

rupi oikuaa añetéva    ha añete'yva, iporâva ha ivaíva, 
                                         
por         verdad+?    y                     y 

tekotevê pehenguéicha oiko oñondivekuéra. 
   
                           junto   +PL


===Random===

* Tetã Amerikagua
  Tetã Amerika+gua
  Country America+OF
 `Countries of America'

* Ysyryguasukuéra Paraguaigua
  Ysyry+guasu+kuéra Paraguai+gua
  River+big+PL Paraguay+OF
 `Big rivers of Paraguay'
